# ── Sommelier Arena — Environment Variables ──────────────────────────────────
#
# There are NO root-level env vars needed for the PartyKit stack.
# All frontend env vars live in front/.env.local (copy from front/.env.local.example).
#
# ── Mode A: Local dev (Astro dev server + PartyKit dev server) ───────────────
#
#   File to create : front/.env.local
#   Content        : PUBLIC_PARTYKIT_HOST=localhost:1999
#   Frontend URL   : http://localhost:4321
#   PartyKit URL   : http://localhost:1999
#
# ── Mode B: Docker (docker-compose --profile full) ───────────────────────────
#
#   No .env.local needed — PUBLIC_PARTYKIT_HOST=localhost:4321 is set
#   as a Docker build arg in docker-compose.yml (baked into the static build).
#   Frontend URL   : http://localhost:4321
#
# ── Production (Cloudflare Pages) ────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   Set PUBLIC_PARTYKIT_HOST in the Cloudflare Pages dashboard:
#   Pages → Project → Settings → Environment variables
#   PUBLIC_PARTYKIT_HOST=your-partykit-project.partykit.dev

# ENV precedence (recommended):
# - Runtime environment (CI, Docker, platform) overrides any values defined in per-service `.env` files.
# - Per-service `.env.example` files document defaults for local dev. Copy them to `.env` for local overrides.
# - Root `.env` is discouraged; prefer per-service `.env` files for clarity.
# - Avoid committing real secrets; use CI/Platform secrets for production values.
